    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. but i keep seeing people call it \"spooky action at a distance.\" why do they use that word specifically? is there something actually weird or unexplainable about how they stay connected?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "\"Spooky action at a distance\" is a phrase coined by Einstein, and it perfectly captures the unsettling nature of entanglement. It's \"spooky\" because the correlation between the particles seems to happen instantaneously, faster than the speed of light, which goes against our everyday intuition about how information should travel. It's not that they are sending a signal, though; it's more like they are part of a single, unified quantum system, even when separated by vast distances. This instantaneous connection is what makes it so mind-bending!",
      "source": "target",
